Package: PARBONET
Type: Package
Title: Simulation of Parameterized Stochastic Boolean Networks
Version: 0.1.0
Description: A useful approach to represent the effect of different perturbing stimuli on Boolean networks is stochastic noise. Some methods to apply stochastic noise on Boolean networks have been presented, which are based on controlling the noise effect using a set of parameters integrated into the update rules. In this package, some useful functions are provided to examine three such parameterization methods: BNp, described by Trairatphisan et al. (2013) <doi:10.1186/1478-811X-11-46>, SDDS, proposed by Murrugarra et al. (2012) <doi:10.1186/1687-4153-2012-5>, and PEW, presented by Deritei et al. (2022) <doi:10.1371/journal.pcbi.1010536>. This package includes modified portions of source code from the 'BoolNet' package.
